:::summary
Epistemology is the branch of philosophy that investigates the nature, sources, and limits of human knowledge. What does it mean to *know* something? How is knowledge different from mere belief or opinion? Can we be certain of anything? These questions, first raised systematically by Plato and sharpened by Descartes, Hume, and Kant, remain among the most debated in all of philosophy — and have profound implications for faith, science, and reason.
:::

